(416, 17, 'wpcf-resume', '1990	B.Sc. degree in Engineering, Major in Mechanical Engineering from the Cooper Union for the Advancement of Science and Art, New York City, USA\r\n\r\n1995	M.Sc. degree in Biomedical Engineering from the Technion – Israel Institute of Technology, Haifa, Israel\r\n\r\n1990-1991	Occupational and Industrial Orthopedic Center (OIOC), NYC – Research and Consulting Engineer. Transit Authority Vibration Project – Performed analysis of vibration exposure to motormen and proposed recommendations to meet the NIH standards.\r\n\r\n1995-1999	BarOn Technologies / InMotion Technologies, Haifa – Project Coordinator for Force Feedback Joystick Project and a member of the R&D Algorithm Team.\r\n\r\n2000-2003	Palti Consultants, Haifa – Performed feasibility analysis and prepared disclosures for various inventions in the medical field.\r\n\r\n2003-2006	Given Imaging, Yokneam – In-House Patent Attorney.\r\n\r\n2005	Licensed as a Patent Agent before the U.S. Patent & Trademark Office.\r\n\r\n2006	Affiliated with Ehrlich & Fenster as a licensed US Patent Agent.\r\n\r\n2007	Licensed as a Patent Attorney before the Israel Patent & Trademark Office.'),
