(654, 296, 'wpcf-email', 'gal@ipatent.co.il'),
(655, 296, 'wpcf-resume_field', '<strong>1986-1993</strong> B.Sc. degree in Biology and Ph.D degree in Genetic Engineering from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem\r\n\r\n<strong>1993-1996</strong> LL.B. degree from the Tel-Aviv University Law School\r\n\r\n<strong>1995-1998</strong> Served as a lecturer at the Faculty of General Studies and the Faculty of Law of the Haifa University. \r\nDuring his academic career, Dr. Ehrlich authored over 25 papers, chapters and books in the fields of Medicine, Biology, Biochemistry, Genetic Engineering, Law and Ethics.\r\n\r\nDr. Ehrlich was honored with the following awards:\r\n<strong>1986</strong> - Released from the IDF with distinction; \r\n<strong>1987-1989</strong>; 3 conseqyutive years - The Hebrew University Deans award; \r\n<strong>1989</strong> - The Golda Meir award; \r\n<strong>1990</strong> - The Polak Family award; \r\n<strong>1994</strong> - The World Association of Medical Law award.\r\n\r\n<strong>Since 1994</strong>, and after having worked as a Patent Attorney for a small patent firm in Israel for six years, Dr. Ehrlich set up his own firm, Ehrlich & Partners, in mid-2000. He immediately set out to complement his expertise with a premier staff of highly talented patent attorneys in other disciplines including, Biotech, Immunology, Agrotechnology, Bioinformatics, Pharmacology, Biochemistry, Chemistry, Physics, Electronics, Electrooptics, Mechanics, Medical Devices, Computer Software, Computer Hardware, Telecommunications, Business Methods, Trademarks, Design Patents, IP Litigation Support, Breeder''s Rights.\r\n\r\nWithin one year, Ehrlich & Partners was the fastest growing patent attorney firm in Israel. The Firm continued to grow exponentially, and since 2005 has been repeatedly ranked by Dun & Bradstreet as the second largest Israeli patent firm in Israel. \r\nIn late 2006, Fenster & Co., the leading Israeli patent firm specializing in the medical devices arts, merged in the firm to form Ehrlich & Fenster. \r\n\r\nEhrlich & Fenster has been recognized by Chambers & Partners and Managing Intellectual Property, as a Band I and Tier 1 Patent Firm in Israel, respectively, for the second and third consecutive year, respectively. \r\n\r\nThe firm has ISO9001:2000, IQC and UKAS certification.\r\nDr. Ehrlich has been recognized by Chambers & Partners and Managing Intellectual Property as a Band I and Tier 1 Patent Attorney in Israel, respectively, for the second consecutive year.\r\n\r\nAccording to Managing Intellectual Property''s Top PCT Filing firms for the year 2009, Ehrlich & Fenster files the highest number of PCT applications amongst all other Israeli firms and is ranked 30th worldwide in PCT filings for the year 2009.\r\n\r\n<strong>In early 2008</strong>, Dr. Ehrlich founded IPTrade, Israel''s leading business platform for selling unexploited hi-technology patents to an eager world of multi-national corporations seeking to grow and diversify their IP portfolios. \r\n\r\nVoluntary Activities:\r\n\r\n<strong>1994</strong>-Present:Member of the Society for Medicine and Law in Israel \r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>-Present Pro bono drafting, filing and prosecuting patent applications for MILBAT, a voluntary organization developing and implementing technological solutions for the disabled..\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong> Drafter of the Policies and Regulations of the Tribunal of the Israeli Equestrian Federation.\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong>-Present Chairman of the Tribunal of the Israeli Equestrian Federation. \r\n\r\n<strong>2010</strong> Member of The Management of the Friends of HaBimah National Theater Society'),
