(679, 307, 'wpcf-resume_field', '1966-1970	B.A. degree, magna cum laude, in Physics from Brandeis University, USA\r\n\r\n1970-1977	Ph.D. degree in Physics from University of California at Berkeley, USA\r\n\r\n1976-1979	Cornell University, Laboratory of Plasma Studies. Postdoctoral Fellow and Research Scientist, research on stability of ion beams and magnetically confined plasmas for fusion energy.\r\n\r\n1979-1990	M.I.T., Plasma Fusion Center, and (1988-89) Dept. of Aeronautics and Astronautics. Research Scientist, theoretical and experimental research on stability, heating and equilibrium of magnetically confined plasmas for fusion energy, and on plasma-spacecraft interactions.\r\n\r\n<strong>1990-1997</strong>	SatCon Technology Corp., Cambridge, MA, USA. Senior Engineer, R&D, including project management, on motor and actuator design, ordinary and superconducting magnet design, magnetic materials, smart materials, vibration control, ion sources, robotics, MEMS, and fluid dynamics, under contracts from the US Dept. of Defense, NASA, and the US Dept. of Energy.\r\n\r\n<strong>1997-2000</strong>	Independent Consultant. R&D on magnetic shielding, fluorescent lights, smart materials, and motor and actuator design, for private industry, the US Dept. of Defense, and NASA.\r\n\r\n<strong>2000-2001</strong> GE Medical Systems, Haifa. Senior Scientist, R&D on magnetic resonance imaging.\r\n\r\n<strong>2001-2006</strong>	Fenster & Co. Patent Attorneys\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>	Affiliated with Ehrlich & Fenster'),
