(780, 317, 'wpcf-email', 'leora@ipatent.co.il'),
(781, 317, 'wpcf-resume_field', '<strong>1990</strong>&nbsp;B.Sc. (Honors) degree in Pharmacology from the Manchester University, UK\r\n\r\n<strong>1991</strong>&nbsp;	M.Sc. degree with distinction in Biochemistry from University College, London, UK\r\n\r\n<strong>1996-1998</strong>&nbsp;	Ph.D. degree in Molecular Embryology from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1999-2004</strong>&nbsp;Scientific editing and grant writing\r\n\r\n<strong>2002-2004</strong>&nbsp;Research in molecular biology. Research project: “Genes and pathways altered in human islets of Langerhans exposed to high glucose concentrations both in vitro and in vivo”.\r\nTechniques included micro array analysis.\r\n\r\nDr. Havin was honored with the following awards:\r\n\r\n<strong>1990</strong>&nbsp;	Pfizer price for the best undergraduate research project in the Biological Sciences\r\n\r\n<strong>2000-2001</strong>&nbsp;	Received Lady Davis Scholarship\r\n\r\n<strong>2004-2006</strong>&nbsp;	Affiliated with Ehrlich & Partners as a Technical Advisor\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>&nbsp;	Affiliated with Ehrlich & Fenster\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>&nbsp; Licensed as a Patent Attorney before the Israel Patent & Trademark Office'),
(788, 313, 'wpcf-email', 'revital@ipatent.co.il'),
(789, 313, 'wpcf-resume_field', '<strong>1986-1989</strong>&nbsp;	B.Sc. degree in Chemistry from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1990-1993</strong>&nbsp;	M.Sc. degree (with distinction) in Organic Chemistry (Major) and Biotechnology (Minor) from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1992</strong>&nbsp;	Employed as a researcher at Ramot, Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1994-1998</strong>&nbsp;	Ph.D. degree in Organic Chemistry from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\nEmployed as an instructor at the Organic Chemistry Students’ Laboratory, Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\nAffiliated with Ehrlich & Partners since October 2000, drafting and prosecuting patent applications in a variety of fields including Biotech, Agrotech, Medicine, Pharmaceuticals, Chemistry and Medical Devices.\r\n\r\n<strong>Since 2004</strong>&nbsp;, Dr. Revital Green serves as the manager of the Chemistry and Pharma department at Ehrlich &Fenster.'),
(790, 307, '_wp_trash_meta_status', 'publish'),
(791, 307, '_wp_trash_meta_time', '1373256284'),
(792, 301, 'wpcf-email', 'Maier@ipatent.co.il'),
(793, 301, 'wpcf-resume_field', '<strong>1989</strong>&nbsp;	B.Sc. (Honors) degree in Mathematics & Physics from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem (Talpiyot Program), Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1994</strong>&nbsp;	M.Sc. degree in Computer Science from Bar-Ilan University, Ramat-Gan, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1994</strong>&nbsp;	Mr. Fenster joined the practice of Sanford T. Colb & Co. as a Patent Attorney trainee. \r\n\r\n<strong>1996</strong>&nbsp;	Mr. Fenster was licensed to practice before the Israel Patent Office as a Patent Attorney and as a Patent Agent at the US Patent & Trademark Office.\r\n\r\n<strong>In 1997</strong>&nbsp;, Mr. Fenster co-founded the firm of Fenster & Company, later to merge in 2006 with the practice of Ehrlich & Partners, becoming Ehrlich & Fenster, Israel’s largest & leading Patent Attorneys firm.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster''s main areas of expertise are in Internet, Computer Science, Image Processing, Bioengineering, Medical Devices and Medical Imaging.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster was involved in drafting and prosecution of thousands of patent applications and in oppositions and litigation support worldwide.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster was involved in drafting opinions about patentability, opinions about freedom to operate and opinions about infringement.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster is an inventor in about 30 patent applications in the fields of software and medical devices (mechanics and electronics)\r\n\r\nInformally, Mr. Fenster has spent the past 17 years meeting with and learning from the leading people in Israeli academia and hi-tech, on a daily basis.\r\nMr. Fenster was a mentor in Talpiyot courses and was involved in the selection of students for the Talpiyot Program\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster lectures in academic and professional forums.'),
(794, 291, 'wpcf-email', 'amit@ipatent.co.il'),
(795, 291, 'wpcf-resume_field', '<strong>1995-1999</strong>&nbsp;	LL.B. degree (Honors) from the Academic College of Law in Ramat-Gan, Israel\r\n\r\n<strong>1999-2000</strong>&nbsp;	Law internship at Carmel Naftali Law Offices, specialized in Commercial and Corporate Law\r\n\r\n<strong>May 2000</strong>&nbsp;	Accepted as a member of the Israel Bar Association\r\n\r\nPrior to his present position at Ehrlich & Fenster, Mr. Ehrlich maintained a varied civil practice. \r\nHe has extensive experience in Corporate Law; Commercial Law; Banking Law, Commercial Litigation. \r\n\r\n<strong>April 2002</strong>&nbsp;	Affiliated with Ehrlich & Partners (later to become Ehrlich & Fenster) as the firm’s Legal Counsel\r\n\r\nAmit Ehrlich is a field-proven attorney with extensive experience in commercial litigation as well as in Intellectual Property, corporate, commercial and banking law.\r\n\r\nAmit is an honors graduate of the Academic College of Law in Ramat-Gan, and maintains a varied civil practice covering a variety of legal domains. His affiliation with Ehrlich & Partners (currently Ehrlich & Fenster) began in 2002. Amit serves as the firm’s chief Legal Counsel.\r\n\r\n<strong>Since 2006</strong>&nbsp;, Amit has focused on assisting patent holders to monetize their patents, including developing and implementing licensing programs and conducting patent sales negotiations for clients ranging from individual inventors to large corporations and founded IPtrade - www.iptrade.com , an Ehrlich initiative for patent monetization where Amit serves as the CEO.'),
